}    
R r = new R (1);     
r.print();      
System.out.println ("Compact Constructor");       
```
In the above code, `this` keyword is used inside a function to refer back to instance of current class in case you need more information about this object or if there's no default constructor available for your record type then it will call compact ctor and print out "compactConstructor".  This way we can add additional logic without changing the existing code.

